8;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m, [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mlast_data_at[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m, and [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140massigned_care_team[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m. The worklist is published via EventBridge ([38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mAC[Amazon EventBridge worklist-bus][38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m) to three subscribers: the Care Management UI back end (AppSync/API Gateway), the Pharmacist review list back end, and the Provider escalation list back end.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     73[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     74[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106mThe sample worklist row in Expected Results confirms the shape. The narrative ("Patient is 4 days post-discharge from a heart failure exacerbation. Weight has trended up about 1 lb per day over the last 3 days (198 to 204; cumulative 6 lbs above the discharge dry weight). Symptom check-in response rate has dropped from a baseline near 85% to about 58%, suggesting the patient may be feeling worse or less engaged. No care management contact has occurred since the day of discharge. Suggested outreach: confirm the weight trend, ask about dyspnea on exertion and orthopnea, ask about diuretic adherence and any recent changes (skipped doses, side effects), ask about diet over the weekend, and consider a same-day add-on with the cardiology transitions clinic or a diuretic adjustment per standing orders.") is explicit clinical content that names the patient's deterioration phenotype, post-acute-event status, recent weight values, recent engagement-pattern changes, and clinical-recommendation-shaped outreach steps.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     75[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     76[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106mThe chapter-3-settled discipline (Recipes 3.1, 3.3, 3.4, 3.5, 3.6, 3.7) is that high-fanout notification channels carry the alert ID only, and the consuming application fetches the full record by ID through an authenticated path so the notification channel never carries PHI. Recipe 3.8's worklist event-bus pattern is structurally similar: three subscribers (UI, pharmacist list, provider escalation list) each fetching from EventBridge. A reader who treats the pseudocode as the implementation specification will produce a system where the full worklist row (including the narrative and the structured outreach suggestions) flows through the EventBridge bus and into each subscriber's downstream stores and logs.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     77[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     78[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106mThe post-discharge specifics amplify the disclosure surface relative to Recipe 3.7. The worklist row names the patient's recent post-discharge weight trajectory, recent engagement pattern, post-acute-event context (heart failure exacerbation, diabetes admission, post-op cardiac), and suggested clinical evaluation steps. For a patient whose cohort is a high-stigma category (substance use disorder transitions, behavioral health post-psychiatric-hospitalization, maternal post-partum, behavioral health), the worklist row's narrative may disclose context that the patient considers more sensitive than other PHI elements. The Variations section names behavioral health transitions as a future cohort (with explicit reference to ecological momentary assessment, medication adherence tracking, social support engagement); a worklist row narrative for a behavioral health post-discharge cohort would name the post-psychiatric-hospitalization context and recent mood scores.[K
