[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    145[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mLocation:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Why-These-Services "Amazon Comprehend Medical for free-text feature extraction" paragraph; "The Technology" Care-management-notes data-source paragraph ("Substantial signal locked in unstructured text; NLP feature extraction can surface it").[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    146[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mProblem:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The recipe correctly identifies that care-management-note features can be extracted via Comprehend Medical and names the use case ("Comprehend Medical extracts conditions, symptoms, medications, and concerns. Optional but useful when the care management interaction feed is text-rich"). But the PHI-handling discipline for the care-management-note ingest path is not specified: where the raw note text lives (presumably in the care-management-tool-of-record like Salesforce Health Cloud, Epic Healthy Planet, or custom CMS tools), how it reaches Comprehend Medical (synchronous DetectEntitiesV2 calls from the feature-engine Lambda, or asynchronous batch jobs against an S3 export from the care management tool), what data Comprehend Medical retains (per the BAA, none beyond the request lifetime), what the audit trail for the entity-extraction call looks like, and whether the extracted entities are stored alongside or instead of the raw note (storing both creates two PHI surfaces for the same content).[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    147[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    148[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106mThe minimum-necessary discipline matters here too: the feature engine probably only needs the structured entities (concerns expressed, medications mentioned, symptom mentions), not the full extracted-entity payload. A naive implementation that stores the full Comprehend Medical output as a feature carries the original note's content forward in structured form, expanding the PHI surface. Same finding shape as Recipe 3.7 S6.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    149[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mFix:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Expand the Comprehend Medical paragraph: "Comprehend Medical's DetectEntitiesV2 is HIPAA-eligible under the BAA; PHI is processed transiently and not retained by Comprehend Medical beyond the request lifetime. The feature-engine Lambda calls DetectEntitiesV2 synchronously with the relevant care-management-note excerpt (not the full note history) and persists only the derived feature flags (concern-mentioned-and-category, medication-mentioned-and-class, symptom-mentioned-and-type); the full Comprehend Medical entity payload is not stored alongside the feature flags. CloudTrail data events on the DetectEntitiesV2 call capture the audit trail. The raw care-management notes themselves remain in the care-management tool of record (the source of truth) and are not duplicated into the feature pipeline beyond the synchronous extraction call."[K
