[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    222[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mDevice-ingest Lambda fails on a malformed RPM webhook payload.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The vendor publishes a new firmware version that adds a previously-unspecified field, the unit-conversion encounters an unhandled unit string (a vendor that ships in stones-and-pounds for UK deployments), the patient master-index resolution times out because the device-to-patient mapping cache is stale. Lambda's default async retry is two retries over six hours and then drop. The result is silently lost: no canonical event reaches the patient state store, no scoring is updated for that patient, the trajectory history is missing the data point. For a program where engagement decay is one of the strongest signals, silently-failing ingestion looks operationally identical to patient disengagement and triggers outreach for a problem that was actually a pipeline failure.[K
