[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    242[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mProblem:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The Cold-Start subsection correctly identifies cold-start as the default state and correctly names four operational mitigations. The Honest Take goes further and is unusually explicit: "The right response is uniform high-touch outreach in the first 72 hours regardless of model output." This is the operational discipline that distinguishes mature programs from immature ones; using a cold-start-unreliable model output to ration day-1 outreach is the failure mode the Honest Take explicitly warns against.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    243[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    244[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106mStep 5's [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mcompute_features[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m correctly implements the cohort-prior fallback for baseline computation ([38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mfeatures[f"{modality}_baseline_source"] = "patient_specific"[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m vs [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140m"cohort_prior"[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m), which is operationally correct for the model's input vector. But Step 7's [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mbuild_worklist[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m does not enforce the "uniform high-touch outreach in the first 72 hours regardless of model output" discipline. The pseudocode sorts rows by tier and composite score within tier and applies capacity caps; cold-start patients (whose [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mdays_post_discharge < 3[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m and whose [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mfeature[*_baseline_source] == "cohort_prior"[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m for most modalities) compete for the same capacity slots as data-rich patients on the basis of their cold-start-unreliable composite score.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    245[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    246[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106mThe consequence: a cold-start patient whose discharge-time risk score was elevated and whose limited day-1-day-2 data happens to look benign (perhaps because the patient has not yet logged a weight, perhaps because the patient is still on the post-discharge crash but the early data hasn't surfaced it) gets a low composite score and falls below the capacity-cap threshold. The day-1 outreach the Honest Take says should happen "regardless of model output" doesn't happen because the model's output rationed it.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    247[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    248[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106mA reader who treats the pseudocode as the implementation specification produces a system that exhibits exactly the failure mode the Honest Take warns against. For a program where the day-1-to-day-3 window is the highest-risk period, this is the operational mitigation that should be architecturally enforced rather than left to the care-management team to remember.[K
