[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    293[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mLocation:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The Honest Take's "Engagement decay is one of the strongest signals" lesson ('"We noticed you stopped checking in; everything okay?" is a script that converts disengagement into a conversation, and the conversation surfaces whichever of the three is happening. Build engagement decay into the model and into the worklist as its own first-class feature.'); "Cold-Start Is the Default State" subsection naming "engagement-first triage" as a cold-start mitigation ("A patient who hasn't logged a single weight by day 3 is escalated to the care management team for outreach, regardless of any other signal"); Step 4 [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mcompute_features[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m (engagement features computed but routed into the composite scoring model only); Step 5 / Step 7 (no engagement-decay-specific worklist pathway).[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    294[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mProblem:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The recipe is unusually clear that engagement decay is one of the strongest signals and that the operational response (a phone call to the disengaged patient) is high-yield because it converts disengagement into actionable information. The Cold-Start subsection further names "engagement-first triage" as a cold-start mitigation in which a patient who hasn't logged a single weight by day 3 is escalated to outreach regardless of any other signal.[K
