[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    361[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mFix:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Update the General Architecture Pattern's "Scoring Service" subsection to name multi-cohort architecture as a first-class concern: "The Scoring Service is per-cohort. Each cohort has its own SageMaker endpoint (hf-anomaly-model, copd-anomaly-model, post-op-cardiac-anomaly-model, etc.), its own calibration curve, its own threshold set, and its own retraining cadence. The Scoring Orchestrator dispatches to the cohort-specific endpoint based on the patient's cohort assignment. Patients in multiple cohorts (a heart-failure patient who also has diabetes) get scored by each relevant cohort-specific model; the worklist construction de-duplicates across cohorts and selects the highest-tier cohort-specific row for the care management worklist. Cohort-specific worklists are also produced for cohort-specific care teams (the heart-failure transitions team works the heart-failure worklist; the diabetes-transitions team works the diabetes worklist)."[K
