[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    427[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mFix:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Expand the HealthLake paragraph: "For programs using HealthLake: configure the FHIR datastore with customer-managed KMS encryption; access HealthLake via VPC endpoint ([38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mcom.amazonaws.{region}.healthlake[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m) so FHIR resource fetches don't traverse the public internet; CloudTrail data events on HealthLake [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mRead*[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m and [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mWrite*[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m operations capture the audit trail; if HealthLake is used as a SMART-on-FHIR backend, scope the OAuth client credentials (the post-discharge-anomaly service principal) to the minimum FHIR resource types and patient compartments needed (Observation for vitals and labs, MedicationAdministration and MedicationDispense for medication context, Encounter for admission and discharge context, Patient for demographics, AllergyIntolerance and Condition for problem-list features). HealthLake's bulk export to S3 supports the offline training pipeline; the export bucket must have customer-managed KMS encryption and lifecycle management aligned to the training data retention policy."[K
